1, MOVIE QUALITY:

As a movie, it is rougher in (course) language then the original TV series. LOL.  I guess in a way - maybe it makes it a bit more realistic.  Justin Nguyen's character is now a female part.

Overall, as a movie, it was fun and intended (atleast this version) for an adult audience.  Please check out the IMDB rating before showing this to youth and children under 14 or 15 years.


2. RIP QUALITY:

Unfortunately, I found this rip to be more like a better DVDRip - quality is not quite upto other 720p rips.

If you just want to watch this regardless of quality, this is fine enough.

Frames flow seem to be jerky. I expected better quality. Sound is not exactly HDef.

I will definitely be looking for a better rip to watch again.

Like some other have already said.  The Audio and Video quality leaves much to be desired; however, I think the movie itself is enjoyable. Especially, if you have every watched 21 Jump Street the TV Series, I would recommend you sit down and watch this movie and you would more than likely enjoy this updated version of the story in a contemporary setting.

Cheers :)
